    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **James Wood** (70.96) stand as our primary anchors. **Mickey Moniak** benefits from an aggressive boost due to his lead-off spot against Freddy Peralta and an exceptional park factor that lifts his profile well above his base projection. Similarly, **James Wood** capitalizes on a high-upside matchup against Taj Bradley, where his role at the top of the lineup combined with solid recent xwOBA metrics makes him an elite play. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (70.58) and **Corbin Carroll** (70.10) also clear the 70-point threshold, with **Vinnie Pasquantino** drawing significant value from a strong platoon advantage against Gavin Williams, while **Corbin Carroll** remains a foundational start despite facing the respectable Bubba Chandler.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Austin Riley** (48.17), who fell just short of the active roster. While his pedigree is strong, his matchup against George Kirby is mitigated by a poor park factor and the elite skill set of the opposing pitcher, which suppressed his efficiency score compared to the more favorable platoon splits offered by **Seiya Suzuki** (67.14) and **Brice Turang** (63.60). **Brice Turang** is particularly intriguing today; while his raw projections are modest, his speed profile against Andre Pallante\u2014combined with a \"Slow SP Delivery\" bonus\u2014makes him a critical component of our quest for stolen bases.\n\nRisk management remains a primary concern as we navigate today\u2019s \"Lineup Pending\" status for the entire roster. We have optimized for the best available data, but users should note the volatility in the **Tyler Soderstrom** start (46.35); while the wind blowing out offers a peripheral boost, his matchup against Cristopher S\u00e1nchez is objectively tough, making him the most precarious member of the starting lineup. Conversely, we are keeping **Jose Caballero** (39.32) sidelined; his matchup against Jacob deGrom presents a bottom-tier environment where his speed upside is negated by the elite efficiency of the opposing arm. Proceed with these projections as current baseline expectations, keeping a close eye on final lineup cards for any last-minute defensive adjustments.",
